		"description": {
			"value": "<p>You transform yourself into a lich or otherwise take on the powers of powerful &amp;reference[undead]. This grants you the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>You count as &amp;reference[undead] in addition to your usual creature type.</p></li><li><p>You are resistant to &amp;reference[necrotic] and &amp;reference[poison] damage.</p></li><li><p>You are immune to the &amp;reference[drained] and &amp;reference[poisoned] conditions.</p></li><li><p>You no longer require to eat, breathe, or sleep. You no longer age and are immune to magical aging.</p></li><li><p>You replace the @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-feats.Item.XEq3S4popmzrJUfw]{&amp;reference[undead] Nature} feat with another level 1 feat if you already have it.</p></li></ul><p>If you want to become a lich specifically, you also perform the Ritual of Endless Night, binding your soul to a powerful object.</p>",
